# ### Secret env variables
# Don't commit to git or share with anyone. Don't bake into docker images or hardcode them inside your code.

# These are the comma seperated secrets. Only the first is taken and you can rotate if compromised. Don't forget to invalidate the old leftovers in the users browser (f.e. old session cookie) if you rotate the secrets.
# Important: Generate new ones when creating your .env file. Use different ones on different environments (dev, stage, prod, ...)
# Important: Use cryptographically secure random bytes and encode as hex or base64. For example, on linux or mac with openssl installed, you can run `openssl rand -hex 64` to generate a 512-bit secret encoded as hex.

